definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah living before Israel's Monarchy, first mentioned at Jos.7.1; 
 son of: Zerah (H2226I); 
 brother of: Ethan (H0387H), Heman (H1968H), Calcol (H3633H) and Dara (H1873); 
 father of: Carmi (H3756H); also called Zimri at 1Ch.2.6; 
Another name of zav.di (זַבְדִּי "Zabdi" H2067G)
 § Zimri = "my music"
 an obscure name mentioned in connection with 'the mingled people' in Jeremiah; may be same as 'Zimran'
